methods.canonicalize:
Canonicalize this tuple.

:param canonicalizer: java.util.function.UnaryOperator<java.lang.Object>
:return: (io.deephaven.db.util.tuples.EmptyTuple) This tuple if already canonical, else a new, canonical tuple of the same type
methods.valueOf:
Returns the enum constant of this type with the specified name.
The string must match exactly an identifier used to declare an
enum constant in this type.  (Extraneous whitespace characters are 
not permitted.)

:param name: (java.lang.String) - the name of the enum constant to be returned.
:return: (io.deephaven.db.util.tuples.EmptyTuple) the enum constant with the specified name
